to the editor i take strong exception to an april 19 letter criticizing the national council of teachers of mathematics for pedagogical backtracking based on national indicators like the national assessment of educational progress and the growing body of research we are seeing the benefits of the mathematics curriculums and instructional methods that have supported the council 's standards in the last decade in its recent update of the standards the council reaffirmed the importance of developing problem solving skills reasoning and conceptual understanding while including attention to basic skills like estimation and mental computation frances r curcio new york april 20 2000 the writer is a professor of mathematics education at new york university

